up the far-flung telecommunications company that once symbolized
Britain's imperial reach. But Wallace quickly began selling pieces
of his company, orchestrating a number of large deals that
culminated with the sale of Cable and Wireless' stake in Cable and
Wireless HKT, the Hong Kong phone company, to Hong Kong's Pacific
Century CyberWorks Ltd. In so doing, Wallace has proved he can defy
