<HEADLINE>
BRAEMAR TO HOST ATP EVENT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVE SHELBURNE  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Braemar Country Club in the San Fernando Valley
neighborhood of Tarzana will be host for a men's professional
tennis tournament this summer, former touring pro Vijay Amritraj
announced Tuesday at Braemar.
</P>
<P>
   Amritraj's First Serve Entertainment has been granted a USTA/ATP
Tour Men's Challenger tournament, which will be played July 10-16
on the 20-court Braemar complex.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a great opportunity to see some of the best young
professional players from various parts of the world,'' said
Amritraj, an Encino resident who plays occasionally at Braemar.
</P>
<P>
   He is especially enthused that San Fernando Valley tennis fans
will get to see upcoming young players ``before they go off and win
the Australian Open.''
</P>
<P>
   Challenger events carry ATP Tour ranking points and in the past
have attracted such pros as Andre Agassi, whose comeback to his
current No. 1 world ranking began with a Challenger event in
Burbank.
</P>
<P>
   Amritraj positioned his event at a time he hopes will attract
more top players for Braemar's 32-man singles draw and the 16-team
doubles competition. It immediately precedes a Challenger
tournament in Northern California and is followed by the annual ATP
Tour event in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   For information on the Braemar competition, phone (818) 988-
5299.
</P>
</TEXT>
