<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE02-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   For those of you who think you've seen the last of Mick Foley,
don't shed too many tears. Despite losing a 'retirement' match with
Triple H in the ``No Way Out'' pay-per-view Sunday, Foley should
return in some capacity for the April 2nd ``Wrestlemania.'' Once
again, WWF fooled the experts with Big Show defeating The Rock,
Chris Jericho losing the Intercontential belt to Kurt Angle and the
Dudley Boyz becoming the new tag team champs. The finishes helped
to make the follow-up ``Raw'' show one of the best this year.
</P>
<P>
   On ``Nitro'' this week, you may have seen the last of Tank
Abbott. His gimmick as the toughman no one can stop will have to be
changed if he remains after his loss to Sid Vicious. Rumors were
hot and heavy that Abbott would be fired after a knife incident in
his match with Big Al at the ``SuperBrawl'' pay-per-view. Don't
expect that, but his chance to be a main eventer has probably
passed.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of passed, did you hear all those boos for Hulk Hogan
on ``Nitro.'' Sure he was bad-mouthing a Minnesota legend in Ric
Flair, but WCW needs to open its ears to the fact fans don't want
to see Hulk Hogan anymore.
</P>
<P>
   D-Lo Brown is getting tired of playing second fiddle to the
Godfather and wants a new gimmick. One problem, his old gimmick
wasn't causing any heat among the fans. A few rumors have surfaced
that the reason why D-Lo dropped both the Intercontential and
European belts was because of the neck injury that he helped cause
to Droz. When D-Lo missed his spot, Droz was injured. Weeks later
he dropped both belts and has been buried in the WWF since.
</P>
<P>
   ECW is looking into making Super Calo a contract offer. He has
worked with the organization on a per appearence basis, but that
could change soon.
</P>
<P>
   Another personality ECW is looking at signing is manager James
Vandenberg. He is currently involved in the storyline with Raven
and Tommy Dreamer. Expect him to become the mentor of the former
ECW tag champs as they feud with the Impact Players. Expect to see
Balls Mahoney return to the ECW soon. He has been working some FMW
shows over in Japan for the past month. The FMW and ECW hope to
continue their trading of talent, which has included Masato Tanaka.
</P>
<P>
   Bert Prentice, who owns Championship Wrestling in the Eastern
Tennessee and Georgia area, pulled out of a deal with WWF to sign
with WCW. Prentice will get wrestlers from the WCW Power Plant to
work some of his shows in those areas.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
