and the massage _ can be split among a foursome. For more
information: The Broadmoor, 1 Lake Ave., Colorado Springs, Colo.
80906; 800-634-7711; www.broadmoor.com.
 &HT;    Aruba Sonesta Resorts has an ``Island Nanny Program'' that
provides a nanny for the duration of the family's stay. The rates
start at $120 per day, and the nanny is on duty from 8:00 a.m. to
midnight for two children. For more information: Aruba Sonesta
Resorts, Orangestad, Aruba; (800) SONESTA; www.arubasonesta.com.
 &HT;    Finally, the 5th Avenue Suites Hotel allows guests to ``Spend
the Night with Doug.'' Ecology-minded guests can request to have a
miniature Douglas Fir, the state tree of Oregon, brought to their
room. Trees that outgrows the hotel will eventually be donated to
Portland's Hoyt Arboretum. For more information: 5th Avenue Suites
Hotel, 506 S.W. Washington, Portland, Ore. 97204; (800) 711-2971;
http://135.145.16.183/5thavenuesuites.com/.
 &HT;    -----
 &HT;    (Everett Potter is a New York City-based free-lance travel
writer.) 
 ---- 
 c.2000 Everett Potter 
