<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    How to lovate hard-to-find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have looked everywhere for a hand and body lotion called
Rose Milk. Is it still manufactured and if so, where can I purchase
it?
</P>
<P>
   _ Laura French, Covington, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: We should all rush out and buy Rose Milk, because the bottle
says it's ``for softer, smoother, younger feeling skin.'' We found
our 8-ounce bottle ($4.96) at Drug Emporium, 2625 Piedmont Road
N.E. (404-233-1201). This lotion has the soft smell of roses and
when applied, is as smooth as milk on the skin, without a greasy
afterfeel, according to a spokeswoman at Lee Pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I recently read in a magazine that almond butter was a
healthful substitute for peanut butter, but I have been
unsuccessful in finding any. Can you help me?
</P>
<P>
   _Christin Chandler, Alpharetta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   And another almond butter request: Where can I find almond
butter? It's like peanut butter but made from almonds.
</P>
<P>
   _Karen Burpo, Alpharetta
</P>
<P>
   A: An almond butter and jelly sandwich, anyone? Usually, nut
butters such as almond butter and cashew butter are available at
health food stores. We found Smooth Almond Butter ($7.99 for a
16-ounce jar) and Crunchy Almond Butter ($5.99 for a 16-ounce jar)
at Whole Foods, 2111 Briarcliff Road N.E. (404-634-7800). Now for
the healthful part. Page Love, a registered Atlanta dietitian and
nutritionist, says that almond butter is not lower in fat than
peanut butter. ``Some brands,'' she says ``are actually higher in
fat, containing 16 to 20 grams of fat per two tablespoons. Peanut
butter, on the other hand, has about 16 grams of fat per two
tablespoons.'' The advantage of a nut butter such as almond butter?
``It's more heart healthy because it is less hydrogenated, which
means less unsaturated fat,'' says Love.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where in Atlanta can I buy the soft drink Cheerwine? Kroger
carried it for awhile, but no more.
</P>
<P>
   _Connie York, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Those of you in Atlanta who like this burgundy-colored soft
drink with the bold cherry taste have little to cheer about. ``We
are happy that people want Cheerwine in Atlanta, but our
distributor there dropped the line last year,'' said Alice Edwards
of Carolina Beverage Corp. The closest places that carry the
carbonated drink are Quality Foods in Habersham and Franklin
counties in Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   However, you Cheerwine addicts can order a case (24 cans, diet
or regular) by sending a check or money order for $22.70 to:
Carolina Beverage Corp., P.O. Box 697, Salisbury, NC 28145. Jump on
the Web site at: www.cheerwine.com for more cheery information.
</P>
<P>
   Q: My wife wants you to track down wax paper sandwich bags. She
says she bought them several years ago at Kroger but cannot find
them anywhere now. Any help you can provide would be much
appreciated.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bernie Hockswender,
</P>
<P>
   Lawrenceville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Although not widely distributed, we managed to find those
elusive wax paper sandwich bags. Known as Reynolds Cut-Rite
Sandwich Bags, they're available through Market Grocery at the
State Farmers Market, 16 Forest Parkway, Building K.
(404-361-8620). Wayne Amos will be glad to special order them for
you. A case of 12 boxes (each box contains 50 bags) is $15;
however, Amos said he would sell customers half a case (six boxes)
for $7.50.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for Levi's Silver Tab loose fit jeans in a
misses size 4. I fear they are not made anymore, so of course they
are the only jeans that really fit me. Are there any retail or
catalog outlets that might carry these now so hard-to-find jeans?
</P>
<P>
   _ Kristin Kelly,
</P>
<P>
   Gainesville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Your fear is well-founded. A spokesman at Levi's said that
the Silver Tab loose fit jean is no longer made in misses sizes;
however, this style is still made in junior sizes, such as 1, 3, 5,
etc. You can probably wear either a size 3 or 5. Look for the
Silver Tabs ($50 a pair) at Rich's stores at Lenox Square, Gwinnett
Place, Southlake Mall, Greenbriar Mall, Town Center Mall and North
Point Mall. The jeans are also available online at jcpenney.com for
the same price.
</P>
