($1.40) a month before they arrived at the Mozdok base. Once there,
the pay was boosted to 400 rubles ($14) a month. Indeed, one of my
enduring impressions of the Russian army is that it seems to be
manned by a legion of beggars _ troops without the money to buy
decent cigarettes, which they are forced to bum from visitors.
