<P>
   ``We all expect to die _ but not like that,'' said Kadi Diallo,
Amadou's grieving mother. Every day she was at the trial of the
four New York policemen accused of killing her son. She wanted to
be there, she said, to be sure that justice was done.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; To bolster your coverage of the aftermath of the acquittal of
the four New York policemen in the Diallo case, we recommend this
profile of Kadi Diallo and her son. By Ted Conover. (slugged:
BC-DIALLO-FAMILY-BACKGROUND)
