<P>
   BUSH-CAMPAIGN (St. Louis) _ A day after swamping Sen. John
McCain in three primaries, Gov. George W. Bush says his Republican
opponent ``ought to be ashamed'' of his campaign's portrayal of
Bush as anti-Catholic. At a rally here, Bush tells supporters he's
``a step closer to ending the Clinton era in Washington D.C.'' By
DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-McCAIN (St. Louis) _ George W. Bush is exuding more
confidence after his three-state sweep that put him solidly ahead
of John McCain in the delegate race. But there also are signs that
he is bitter about the tone of the campaign so far. By R.G.
RATCLIFFE and GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-BRADLEY (Los Angeles) _ Bill Bradley, who is still winless
in his quest for the Democratic presidential nomination, is
scheduled to debate Al Gore tonight in Los Angeles. By CRAGG HINES
and BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SOCIAL-SECURITY (Washington) _ Senior citizens win a major
victory as the House votes overwhelmingly to repeal a law that
docks the Social Security checks of retirees who keep working if
they earn more than $17,000 a year. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   ELIAN-CONGRESS (Washington) _ A Miami cousin of six-year-old
Elian Gonzalez says his father has secretly signaled from Havana
that he wants his son to remain in the United States. In testimony
before the Senate Judiciary Committee, the cousin, Marisleyis
Gonzalez, says the boy's father Juan has indicated on the phone
several times that he does not want the boy returned to him in
Cuba. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   PUERTO-RICO-STATEHOOD (Washington) _ Puerto Rico Gov. Pedro
Rossello lobbies Congress to approve a White House request for $2.5
million to underwrite a federal effort that Rossello hopes would
lead to Puerto Rico becoming the nation's 51st state. The White
House-backed effort was a little-noticed sweetener in a deal that
Rossello struck with President Clinton last month to end a long
stalemate over Navy bombing on Puerto Rico's Vieques island. By
STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Kissimmee, Fla.) _ Daryle Ward emerged as one of the
key players for the Houston Astros during their push toward a third
consecutive NL Central title last season. But this spring, Ward
finds himself on the outside looking in as the Astros try to
formulate their outfield lineup for their debut season at Enron
Field. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   With: BBN-LOPEZ-COLUMN
