<P>
   BBO-BRAVES-ROCKER (New York) _ Baseball's arbitrator slashed by
about two-thirds Commissioner Bud Selig's suspension of John
Rocker, the Atlanta Braves pitcher, who in a magazine interview had
disparaged foreigners, gays and members of minorities. Rocker can
begin spring training immediately. Selig had suspended Rocker for a
total of 73 days, all 45 days of spring training and the first four
weeks of the season. But the arbitrator, Shyam Das, cut in half, to
two weeks, the in-season part of the suspension. And he eliminated
the remainder of the spring training suspension, ending Rocker's
exile at 13 days. Das also virtually eliminated the $20,000 fine
that Selig levied, reducing it to $500, which the Players
Association contended was the most Rocker could be fined under the
collective bargaining agreement. By Murray Chass.
</P>
