   GRAPEFRUIT GROWERS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ For those who believe the joy in farming has
disappeared, we'd like to introduce Clare and Bill Braden. They
call themselves fruit peddlers. We'd say they're symbols of Texas
spirit. Despite a late-life entry into the business, despite a
devastating freeze, despite farming as corporate culture, this
couple has made a success of the orchard business in one short
decade. By BEVERLY BUNDY. Story has moved in ``d'' food and dining
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GRAPEFRUIT PIE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The Rio Grande Valley has its share of Texas staples _
Tex-Mex, southern-fried blue plates and barbecue. But the Valley is
also home to grapefruit pie, a dessert that showcases the ruby red
fruit of the surrounding citrus groves. The pie, in its homey
gelatin-based guise, has vague roots. But it was at Ferrell's Pit,
a barbecue spot in Mission, that it gained commercial success. By
BEVERLY BUNDY. Story has moved in ``d'' food and dining category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
