<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Did you see that list of big-league baseball drug
suspensions in the paper the other day? Instead of pre-game
meetings to discuss opposing hitters and pitchers, maybe baseball
teams should conduct mandatory meetings of Narcotics Anonymous.
It's not just baseball, of course. Football has its Lawrence
Taylors and Leon Letts. And basketball's Dallas Mavericks gave the
world Roy Tarpley. But baseball lays claim to a breathtaking Hall
of Shame when it comes to substance abusers. Take Darryl Strawberry
_ please. By BILL THOMPSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
