<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``In the last year I've lost 33 pounds. ... I am a fat person
and I accept my fat completely, so I feel strange jogging to lose
weight. It's almost as if it is something which is against my
values to want to be less fat. But I am a diabetic and I had to
reduce my blood sugar, which is connected to being fat. Most people
are proud when they lose weight. I find myself apologizing.''
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; David Crosby &LR;  to Personals &LR; ' &LR;  spy  &UR; Baird Jones &LR; , at an HBO
premiere party in New York for ``If These Walls Could Talk 2.''
</P>
</TEXT>
