<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-01 19:36 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3673 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u w BC-ELIAN-CONGRESS-HNS &LR;      03-01 0617
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ELIAN-CONGRESS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     COUSIN TELLS SENATE THAT ELIAN'S FATHER WANTS BOY TO STAY IN
U.S. 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By MARK HELM  
 &HT;     c.2000 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The Miami woman who has been caring for 6-year-old
Elian Gonzalez said Wednesday the boy's father has indicated that
he wants his son to remain in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   In testimony before the Senate Judiciary Committee, Marisleyis
Gonzalez said Juan Gonzalez has suggested in several phone
conversations that he does not want the boy sent back to Cuba. She
said the father told her during one call: ``I appreciate everything
you're doing for my son. Do you understand what I'm trying to tell
you? Do you understand?''
</P>
<P>
   Marisleyis Gonzalez, who is Elian's cousin, said she believes
the father was trying to tell her that he wants her to fight to
keep the boy in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   However, Juan Gonzalez has publicly said that he wants his son
returned to his homeland. He has appeared with Cuban leader Fidel
Castro appealing for the repatriation of the boy.
</P>
<P>
   Elian, who was 5 years old at the time, was found clinging to an
inner tube off the coast of Florida on Nov. 25 after the boat
carrying him to the United States capsized, killing his mother,
Elizabet Brotons Rodriguez, her boyfriend and nine other people.
</P>
<P>
   The Immigration and Naturalization Service has ruled that the
boy should be returned to his father in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   However, Lazaro Gonzalez, the boy's great-uncle, has sued the
INS in federal court in Miami, challenging the agency's decision.
U.S. District Judge K. Michael Moore plans to hear arguments in
that case next week.
</P>
<P>
   Justice Department spokeswoman Carol Florman said Attorney
General Janet Reno ``continues to believe that this child belongs
with his father who continues to have sole legal authority over the
boy.''
</P>
<P>
   She added that the attorney general also ``hopes the case can be
resolved quickly.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Congress is considering legislation sponsored by Sen.
Connie Mack, R-Fla., that would confer citizenship on Elian.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking before the Judiciary Committee, the estranged daughter
of Fidel Castro urged the United States not to deport the boy to a
``land dominated by fear.''
</P>
<P>
   ``You cannot allow this unilateral victory on behalf of a
dictator,'' said Alina Fernandez, an out-of-wedlock daughter who
fled Cuba in 1993 and is one of her father's fiercest critics.
</P>
<P>
   She said that the rights of parents and family ``do not exist''
under Castro's Communist government and that Elian Gonzalez's
family in Cuba is being ``used'' and ``manipulated'' to generate
anti-American sentiment.
</P>
<P>
   Senate Judiciary Committee Chairman Orrin Hatch, R-Utah, who
favors Mack's bill, said the dispute over Elian is not just a
``custody matter, but a case where one of the options considered is
returning this child to one of the last prison nations in the
world.''
</P>
<P>
   But Sen. Patrick Leahy of Vermont, the panel's senior Democrat,
said the committee was making a mistake trying to intervene in an
immigration case that is before a federal court.
</P>
<P>
   ``This whole matter has been politicized from the beginning, and
it's time we let the courts do their job,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Elian Gonzalez did not make the trip to Washington.
</P>
<P>
   ``He is going to school and trying to lead a normal life,''
Roger Bernstein, the lawyer for the boy's Miami relatives, said in
a statement. ``We want a resolution to this.''
</P>
<P>
   In January, the boy's grandmothers came to the United States to
appeal to Congress to allow Gonzalez to be returned to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Mark Helm can be reached at 202-298-6920 or by e-mail at
mark(at)hearstdc.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
