<HEADER>
A3674 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a BC-REVDOLLAR-JAIL02-COX     03-01 0320
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-REVDOLLAR-JAIL02-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    No arrest of minister so far in Holyfield case
 &HT;    By Ralph Ellis
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Rev. Creflo Dollar, leader of the 20,000-member
World Changers Ministries, is a wanted man.
</P>
<P>
   Fayette County sheriff's deputies have been instructed to put
Dollar in the county jail until Dollar agrees to give a deposition
in the Evander Holyfield divorce case.
</P>
<P>
   As of late Wednesday afternoon, no arrest had been made.
</P>
<P>
   Fayette County Superior Court Judge Ben Miller had found Dollar
in contempt in December after Dollar refused to provide information
about how much money ex-heavyweight champion Holyfield gave to
World Changers church in College Park.
</P>
<P>
   Dollar appealed, but the Georgia Supreme Court dismissed the
appeal Friday on a technicality. Miller told deputies to find
Dollar.
</P>
<P>
   Lecora Bowen, Dollar's lawyer, could not be reached for comment
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   She previously said Dollar should not be deposed because of the
separation of church and state, pastor-parishioner privilege,
several state and biblical laws. Dollar has given sermons in which
he vowed not to release the information because he doesn't want to
facilitate a divorce.
</P>
<P>
   Miller sent a letter saying Dollar would not be jailed if he
called Janice Holyfield's lawyer and promised to appear at a
deposition. John Mayoue, Janice Holyfield's lawyer, said Wednesday
he had not heard from Dollar's lawyer.
</P>
<P>
   State law says a person can be jailed up to 20 days and fined
$500 for civil contempt. According to the Georgia attorney
general's office, a judge can renew the contempt citation.
</P>
<P>
   Dollar ruffled feathers last year when he gave $1,000 checks to
100 Fulton County police officers. The officers were ordered to
return the money but about half the officers have not done so,
police said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-01-00 1936EST &QL; 
