<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-CALIF-BIGSUR-3RDTAKE-$ADV05-NYT </SLUG>
  
 UNDATED: named Zenith. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   From aerobics to yoga
</P>
<P>
   The Post Ranch Inn is on Highway 1, Big Sur, Calif. 93920, (800)
527-2200, fax (831) 667-2824; on the Web at www.postranchinn.com.
It's about four hours by car from San Francisco.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Room rates range from $395 to $700 (for a house that can
accommodate as many as six adults, $50 for each additional person
after the first two); after April 1, rates will be $455 to $755.
There is a 10.5 percent hotel tax. Tips are at guests' discretion.
For a weekend stay, a Friday and Saturday two-night minimum is
required. Guests are discouraged from bringing children.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Spa services range from $85 for an hourlong facial to $180 for a
two-hour aromatherapy massage. There is one yoga class daily, a tai
chi class on Sunday, and a small gym with exercise equipment that
shares a building with Post Ranch Mercantile, a shop selling home
furnishings and bath products used at the inn as well as the usual
caps and T-shirts. Dinner at Sierra Mar, with a glass of wine, is
about $75 a person. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Bernardus Lodge is at 415 Carmel Valley Road, Carmel Valley,
Calif. 93924, (888) 648-9463, fax (831) 659-3529,
www.bernardus.com. From San Francisco it's about two and a half
hours by car. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Room rates vary with the season and range from $245 to $725. My
two rooms were ``premium view,'' usually $345, but discounted to
$245 because the spa had not been completed. There is a 10.5
percent hotel tax, plus a $15 a day resort fee that covers
housekeeping, bell, concierge and valet tips.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The 5,300-square-foot spa building has since opened, only to spa
guests. Treatments and exercise classes are expensive. Treatments
range from $75 for a 25-minute reflexology session to $420 for the
Vineyard Romance, 100 minutes for two people that includes the
Harvest Crush, a grapeseed and red wine scrub, an open-air lavender
bath and full body massage.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Regular exercise classes haven't begun yet; the lodge plans to
have water aerobics, tai chi, stretching and yoga in full swing by
summer. Group classes for six people or more will cost $55, $65 for
groups of two to five. Private instruction is also available, for
$95 for 50 minutes.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   There are also two tennis courts, and boccie and croquet courts
for use by guests. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Children are accepted, but there are no programs for them; this
is a retreat designed for adults. Dinner at the Marinus, the
hotel's casually elegant restaurant, is about $75 a person with
wine.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Admission to the Bernardus tasting room is free for guests.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
