 By KATHERINE BUTLER  
 c.2000 The Independent, London  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (UNDATED) _ Rosita Pedro was born in a tree Wednesday as the
brown crocodile-infested floodwaters of Mozambique's Limpopo River
swirled around her and her terrified mother, Sofia.
</P>
<P>
   In the midst of Mozambique's worst floods in living memory, with
death and destruction all around them, Sofia's survival, let alone
her infant's daughter's safe delivery was a miracle.
</P>
<P>
   Like hundreds of thousands of other desperate Mozambicans, a
